{
  "stem": "20580.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Says, everything is going.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He likes yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Then they send me to yeshiva [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then I-- and eventually the Yeshiva with the Russian were nice, they says, but it's not.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I know a little bit of Russian, but not a big scholar.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They send me away to [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] was the Russian yeshiva.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They call it, in Hebrew, [NON-ENGLISH], which is written in the books, still books today.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The one from the rabbis write in-- in-- in the-- the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that Yeshiva was there, well, a couple months.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I have to bear payos.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I have to bear tzitzits.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You know the way it is.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It's not-- not necessary to wear it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I-- you have to davening exactly with the-- [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You know the way it is.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But I accept it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But when I came home for a visit Passover, as my mother was going to her cousins, which they're very intelligent.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The name-- I'll tell you the name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] Schechter.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] Flom, I had at that time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I came to there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He says, listen, a rabbi, he wouldn't be.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He doesn't like it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he wouldn't be.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To-- to give him education like in the Jewish school, learn archaeology, biology, with all of that stuff with Darwin's theory about evolution, he accept it very nice.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He likes it, but what's at the end of it?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He wouldn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The only way, he have to learn a trade.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What kind trade?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Tailor, this, that, I don't like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I went to a tannery, tannery, tanning the leather.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then, Offenbach, in Germany, it was the biggest-- the biggest tannery in the world, they say.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The biggest chemistry they have there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It cost, at that time, I paid 120 dollars, a passport, a this, a that.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
